{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775853689523,"sessionID":"ses_286df48eeffe33EemLEUIsVZcH","part":{"id":"prt_d7920d38e001WFG9SuYyRUdE8h","messageID":"msg_d7920c9b1001WxHxTXR9k1MfCZ","sessionID":"ses_286df48eeffe33EemLEUIsVZcH","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_89d68dad3fa5475fad40d88e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-015/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-015/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-015 — PicoD 命令执行 API\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the PicoD command execution API in `pkg/picod`.\n6: \n7: ## Base Specifications\n8: \n9: - **AR**: AR-015\n10: - **Module**: `pkg/picod`\n11: - **Language**: Go\n12: - **Size**: M\n13: - **Base Spec**: `deployment/client-go.md` (client-go library), `code-execution/spec.md`\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## Background\n18: \n19: PicoD is an HTTP daemon that runs commands inside a configurable workspace jail, manages workspace files, and exposes a health endpoint with JWT (RSA)-protected APIs. This delta covers the server implementation in `pkg/picod` and CLI in `cmd/picod`.\n20: \n21: ---\n22: \n23: ## Requirements\n24: \n25: ### AR-015-001: Command execution API\n26: \n27: - **GIVEN** a valid JWT and JSON body with non-empty `command` and empty `timeout`\n28: - **WHEN** the client calls `POST /api/execute`\n29: - **THEN** the server uses a default timeout of 60 seconds, runs the command, and returns `stdout`, `stderr`, `exit_code`, `duration` (seconds), `start_time`, and `end_time` as JSON\n30: \n31: ### AR-015-002: Custom timeout execution\n32: \n33: - **GIVEN** a valid JWT and JSON body where `timeout` is a non-empty string parseable by Go `time.ParseDuration` (e.g. \"30s\", \"500ms\")\n34: - **WHEN** the client calls `POST /api/execute`\n35: - **THEN** the server uses that duration for the command context timeout\n36: \n37: ### AR-015-003: Timeout exceeded\n38: \n39: - **GIVEN** execution exceeds the context deadline\n40: - **WHEN** the context is cancelled\n41: - **THEN** the response `exit_code` SHALL be `124` (`TimeoutExitCode`) and stderr SHALL include a message that the command timed out with the timeout length in seconds (integer formatting)\n42: \n43: ### AR-015-004: Invalid timeout format\n44: \n45: - **GIVEN** `timeout` is non-empty and not a valid duration\n46: - **WHEN** the client calls `POST /api/execute`\n47: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 400 with JSON `error` describing invalid timeout format and `code` 400\n48: \n49: ### AR-015-005: Empty command\n50: \n51: - **GIVEN** JSON binds successfully but `command` has length zero\n52: - **WHEN** the client calls `POST /api/execute`\n53: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 400 with `error` \"command cannot be empty\" and `code` 400\n54: \n55: ### AR-015-006: Working directory inside workspace\n56: \n57: - **GIVEN** `working_dir` is non-empty\n58: - **WHEN** the server resolves it with the same path-safety rules as file APIs\n59: - **THEN** `cmd.Dir` is set to the sanitized absolute path; if resolution fails, the server responds HTTP 400 with `error` prefixed by \"Invalid working directory: \"\n60: \n61: ### AR-015-007: Environment augmentation\n62: \n63: - **GIVEN** `env` is non-empty\n64: - **WHEN** the command runs\n65: - **THEN** `cmd.Env` is the current process environment plus additional entries `key=value` for each map entry\n66: \n67: ### AR-015-008: Malformed JSON request\n68: \n69: - **GIVEN** the body is not valid JSON for `ExecuteRequest`\n70: - **WHEN** binding fails\n71: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 400 with `error` from the binder and `code` 400\n72: \n73: ---\n74: \n75: ## Scenario: File Upload API\n76: \n77: ### AR-015-010: Multipart file upload\n78: \n79: - **GIVEN** `Content-Type` has prefix `multipart/form-data`, form field `path` is set, and form file `file` is present\n80: - **WHEN** the client posts to `POST /api/files`\n81: - **THEN** the server creates parent directories with mode `0755`, writes the uploaded stream to a sanitized path, applies mode from form field `mode` via `parseFileMode` (default `0644` when empty/invalid/exceeds max), and responds HTTP 200 with `FileInfo` using `path` as relative to the workspace root\n82: \n83: ### AR-015-011: Multipart missing path or file\n84: \n85: - **GIVEN** multipart request with empty `path` or missing/unreadable `file`\n86: - **WHEN** the handler runs\n87: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 400 with an appropriate `error` and `code` 400\n88: \n89: ### AR-015-012: JSON Base64 upload\n90: \n91: - **GIVEN** non-multipart request with JSON `path` and `content` (Base64 standard encoding) required\n92: - **WHEN** the client posts to `POST /api/files`\n93: - **THEN** the server decodes content, creates directories, writes the file with `parseFileMode` on `mode`, and responds HTTP 200 with `FileInfo` (relative `path`)\n94: \n95: ### AR-015-013: Invalid Base64 content\n96: \n97: - **GIVEN** JSON upload with invalid Base64 in `content`\n98: - **WHEN** decoding fails\n99: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 400 with `error` describing invalid base64 and `code` 400\n100: \n101: ---\n102: \n103: ## Scenario: File Listing API\n104: \n105: ### AR-015-020: Directory listing successful\n106: \n107: - **GIVEN** `path` refers to an existing directory inside the workspace\n108: - **WHEN** the client calls `GET /api/files?path=<dir>`\n109: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 200 with `files` as an array of `FileEntry` objects (`name`, `size`, `modified`, `mode`, `is_dir`), skipping entries where `entry.Info()` fails\n110: \n111: ### AR-015-021: Missing path query parameter\n112: \n113: - **GIVEN** the `path` query parameter is absent or empty\n114: - **WHEN** the client calls `GET /api/files`\n115: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 400 with `error` \"Missing 'path' query parameter\" and `code` 400\n116: \n117: ### AR-015-022: Directory not found\n118: \n119: - **GIVEN** sanitized path does not exist\n120: - **WHEN** `os.ReadDir` fails with not exist\n121: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 404 with `error` \"Directory not found\" and `code` 404\n122: \n123: ---\n124: \n125: ## Scenario: File Download API\n126: \n127: ### AR-015-030: File download successful\n128: \n129: - **GIVEN** the wildcard path resolves to a regular file inside the workspace\n130: - **WHEN** the client calls `GET /api/files/<path>`\n131: - **THEN** the server sets `Content-Description` to `File Transfer`, `Content-Transfer-Encoding` to `binary`, `Content-Disposition` to `attachment; filename=\"<basename>\"`, `Content-Type` from `mime.TypeByExtension` or `application/octet-stream`, and returns the file body\n132: \n133: ### AR-015-031: Path escapes workspace\n134: \n135: - **GIVEN** the requested path fails `sanitizePath`\n136: - **WHEN** the client calls the download endpoint\n137: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 400 with `error` describing access denied / workspace jail\n138: \n139: ### AR-015-032: Path is a directory\n140: \n141: - **GIVEN** the path exists but is a directory\n142: - **WHEN** the client downloads\n143: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 400 with `error` \"Path is a directory, not a file\" and `code` 400\n144: \n145: ### AR-015-033: File not found\n146: \n147: - **GIVEN** the path does not exist\n148: - **WHEN** stat fails with not exist\n149: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 404 with `error` \"File not found\" and `code` 404\n150: \n151: ---\n152: \n153: ## Scenario: Health Endpoint\n154: \n155: ### AR-015-040: Health check unauthenticated\n156: \n157: - **GIVEN** no `Authorization` header\n158: - **WHEN** the client calls `GET /health`\n159: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 200 with `status` \"ok\", `service` \"PicoD\", `version` \"0.0.1\", and `uptime` as a string from `time.Since(server start)`\n160: \n161: ---\n162: \n163: ## Scenario: JWT Authentication\n164: \n165: ### AR-015-050: Missing or malformed Authorization header\n166: \n167: - **GIVEN** missing header, or a header that is not exactly two space-separated parts with first part `Bearer`\n168: - **WHEN** an `/api` route is hit\n169: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 401 with JSON including `error`, `code` 401, and `detail` explaining the failure\n170: \n171: ### AR-015-051: Invalid or expired JWT\n172: \n173: - **GIVEN** a Bearer token that fails verification (signature, expiry, etc.) with options `WithExpirationRequired`, `WithIssuedAt`, and `WithLeeway(1 minute)`\n174: - **WHEN** the middleware runs\n175: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 401 with `error` \"Invalid token\", `code` 401, and `detail` containing the verification error\n176: \n177: ### AR-015-052: Public key required at startup\n178: \n179: - **GIVEN** `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` is unset or does not decode to an RSA public key in PEM form\n180: - **WHEN** `NewServer` initializes\n181: - **THEN** the process SHALL log a fatal error and not continue serving\n182: \n183: ---\n184: \n185: ## Scenario: Server Configuration\n186: \n187: ### AR-015-060: CLI defaults\n188: \n189: - **GIVEN** `-port` and `-workspace` use program defaults\n190: - **WHEN** the binary starts\n191: - **THEN** `port` defaults to `8080`, `workspace` defaults to empty (resolved to CWD), and Gin runs in `ReleaseMode` with `Logger` and `Recovery` middleware globally\n192: \n193: ### AR-015-061: Server starts on configured port\n194: \n195: - **GIVEN** CLI flags are parsed with `-port` and `-workspace`\n196: - **WHEN** the binary runs\n197: - **THEN** the HTTP server SHALL listen on `\":<port>\"` with `ReadHeaderTimeout` of 10 seconds\n198: \n199: ---\n200: \n201: ## Scenario: Build and Integration\n202: \n203: ### AR-015-070: Go build succeeds\n204: \n205: - **GIVEN** complete implementation in `pkg/picod` and `cmd/picod`\n206: - **WHEN** running `go build ./cmd/picod`\n207: - **THEN** compilation SHALL succeed without errors\n208: - **AND** the binary SHALL be generated\n209: \n210: ### AR-015-071: Unit tests pass\n211: \n212: - **GIVEN** implementation with test coverage for handlers\n213: - **WHEN** running `go test ./pkg/picod/...`\n214: - **THEN** all tests SHALL pass\n215: - **AND** test coverage SHALL exceed 60%\n216: \n217: ### AR-015-072: HTTP server runs\n218: \n219: - **GIVEN** valid configuration with `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` set to a valid RSA public key\n220: - **WHEN** the binary starts\n221: - **THEN** the server SHALL start and respond to `GET /health`\n222: - **AND** `/api/*` routes SHALL require JWT authentication\n223: \n224: ---\n225: \n226: ## References\n227: \n228: - Base spec: `deployment/client-go.md`\n229: - Design: `code-execution/design.md`\n230: - Spec: `code-execution/spec.md`\n231: - Module: `pkg/picod`\n232: - Command: `cmd/picod`\n\n(End of file - total 232 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-015 — PicoD 命令执行 API\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the PicoD command execution API in `pkg/picod`.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-015\n- **Module**: `pkg/picod`\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: M\n- **Base Spec**: `deployment/client-go.md` (client-go library), `code-execution/spec.md`\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nPicoD is an HTTP daemon that runs commands inside a configurable workspace jail, manages workspace files, and exposes a health endpoint with JWT (RSA)-protected APIs. This delta covers the server implementation in `pkg/picod` and CLI in `cmd/picod`.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-015/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775853689500,"end":1775853689521}}}}
